{
    "speeches": [
        {
            "speakername": "Munira Wilson",
            "rewritten_speech": "Hey everyone 🎓, I'm pushing for a new law to make sure every school has a mental health pro on hand. Why? Because kids are struggling big time with mental health, and getting help is a nightmare! 😢 Parents and headteachers keep telling me how bad it is, with teachers acting like superheroes without the backup they need. 🚨 Mental health for youngsters was a mess even before COVID-19, and now it's worse! 

Did you know 1 in 5 kids, aged 7-16, probably has a mental health issue? Imagine if that many had a physical illness like diabetes—there'd be uproar! We need to treat mental and physical health the same. Early support is super important. Half of all lifetime mental health conditions show up by 14. Jumping in early can stop things getting worse. 

There are stories across the board, like Nicole, who waited ages for help that didn't come, leaving her feeling stuck and hurting. The government doesn't even keep track of how much they're spending on young people's mental health. Truth is, they seem to see kids as a 'money drain,' which is just wrong. Investing in kids' mental health is investing in our future. 💡

Mental Health Support Teams (MHSTs) in schools are a start but they're stretched too thin! For crying out loud, half of secondary and three-quarters of primary schools haven't got any MHSTs. The job lands on teachers who are already swamped. Some schools scrimping for any support now have to cut back. That's why my plan is for this to be a funded requirement, using the 'polluter pays' idea by slapping more taxes on social media giants who added to these problems.

Missing out on school because of mental health is a big deal. New data shows it. Over a fifth of kids waiting for mental health support have skipped more than half a year of school! This leads to more problems like stopping hobbies and avoiding friends. Schools see these kids stuck, barely leaving home, and know that onsite mental health help could've kept them in class. It's happening too much. 

This is our chance to fix things: put a mental health pro in every school, make support easy to get and stop problems early. Long term, it'll help the NHS save money, but more importantly, it helps kids grow up healthier and happier. 🎯 This proposal is vital for our future—a message reinforced by groups like YoungMinds and Barnardo’s. It's time to act. Thanks to everyone who supported this, especially the brave young people, parents, and teachers sharing their stories. Let's make this change. 🙌"
        }
    ]
}

