            "rewritten_speech": "Just wanted to talk about the awful thing that happened in Southport yesterday. It's beyond words really. Some little kids were just dancing and celebrating their summer break and then tragedy struck. We lost three young ones: Bebe, Elsie, and Alice. 💔 The families have shared some touching words, like from Alice's family: ‘Keep smiling and dancing, our princess.’ \n\nSix more kids and two adults are in the hospital. Our hearts go out to everyone affected. I was in Southport today with the police, fire services, and MPs, laying flowers at the spot. The PM is in town, too. Those first responders were absolute heroes, even some off-duty NHS folks jumped in to help. 🙌 It’s so important to recognise the toll it takes on them; Southport's community spirit is tops! \n\nWe're standing by the police as they lead a huge investigation, backed by counter-terrorism cops. They nabbed a 17-year-old at the scene and don't think there’s any more threat. Let’s not spread gossip online, as it can mess with investigations. We’ve got to respect the grieving families and be patient as justice takes its course. There’s a vigil tonight, and Southport is showing such resilience and solidarity. Our thoughts are with the victims and their families. 🌟"
