            "rewritten_speech": "Hey folks, I'm moving for the Bill to get its second reading. Honestly, we should be super proud of our young people in England. Back in 2010, we were ranked 27th in maths and 25th in reading. Now we're 11th and 13th! All schools in my area are now rated good or outstanding, which wasn’t the case 14 years ago. 🎉 But here's the issue: student absence is a big deal. Even post-COVID, over a million kids are persistently absent. School’s not just about making friends; it’s critical for skills and opportunities later in life. Research shows missing even 10% of school massively affects grades: three-quarters of regular attendees get five good GCSEs compared to just one-third of those who miss school often. Even minor drops in attendance have serious effects, as a local school pointed out. It's time to make sure all kids are in school as much as possible. 📚"
        },
        {
            "speakername": "Philip Dunne",
