        },
        {
            "speakername": "Simon Hoare",
            "rewritten_speech": "This is my first time attending a debate like this, and wow, the raw emotion here is eye-opening. Thanks to everyone who spoke today; it's been a real privilege to hear it all. \n\nThe theme 'fragility of freedom' rings true not just in far-off places but right here in our home turf. Sometimes we get a bit comfy with our freedoms, but we gotta stay vigilant and protect them, alongside being brave and vocal about it! We need courage for hope and opportunity, in defending what’s precious.\n\nSeeing faces in the Holocaust memory spaces like Auschwitz gives a human touch to these incomprehensible numbers. Hard to forget those haunting images once you've seen them. 😔 Let's remember: man’s inhumanity is an eternal shame. We owe it to the people of the Jewish community—who have had to adapt and fight for their place for centuries—to stand up. Working together, though, we can ensure peace and freedom are sustained.\n\nTo everyone sharing their personal experiences, from 7 October grieves to Holocaust enactments: your courage is everything. 'Never again' means speaking up against hate wherever we see it. Let's preserve the legacy of such memorials and remind people, future and present, that we’re committed to this cause together."
