            "rewritten_speech": "Hey everyone, I'm here to pitch a new Bill focusing on giving teachers the right training to spot autism early. Why's this crucial? Well, the numbers speak for themselves: Less than half of autistic kids are happy at school, and a whopping 73% think their teachers don’t get them. Only 20% can hit grade 5 or above in English and Maths GCSEs compared to 52% of all kiddos. Plus, autistic children are twice as likely to be kicked out of school! 😓

