            "speakername": "Thomas Tugendhat",
            "rewritten_speech": "Thanks, my mate. Keeping peaceful protests and free speech alive is top of our list, no doubt. You've asked good questions about face coverings. Police will have the call on when people need to show their faces. As for fireworks, the rules will target those involved in protests, not just any passersby around events like Diwali or Bonfire Night. \n \nAbout war memorials, they're sacred. So we get why people are upset when they’re messed with. Lastly, on counter-extremism, we're strengthening policies. We're working on defining extremism and making sure groups that pose threats are tackled properly. We're on it!"
