{
    "speeches": [
        {
            "speakername": "Kenny MacAskill",
            "rewritten_speech": "Hey folks, let's talk about this new Bill I'm introducing, which aims to make sure all Scotland national football matches are available on free TV. 🎉 At the moment, if you want to watch Scotland play in the World Cup or the UEFA European Championship, most of the games aren't free. This is like charging a poll tax on Scots who just wanna cheer for their national team without breaking the bank. 🏴⚽

I've been lucky to witness some incredible Scotland games in the past, and we've got a team full of talent like Andy Robertson and Scott McTominay. But too many Scots are stuck at home, unable to watch because it's all locked up behind Viaplay's paywall, which charges £180 a year. With everything else so expensive, that's a cost many just can't handle. It's not fair and not how it should be! 🤯

In lots of European countries, and even in other parts of the UK, such as England, matches are free to watch. Outside of major tournaments, even friendly matches in Scotland are behind Viaplay's paywall, unlike England's, which are on Channel 4 for everyone to see. Totally unfair, right?

Women’s football and under-21 matches are no better. England’s women’s games are on big channels with wider reach, while Scotland’s are tucked away on BBC Alba—a channel not many can access. ⚖️

Some folks might blame the Scottish Football Association (SFA) for this situation, but I don’t. They’ve got to fund Scottish football at all levels, from grassroots to the national team. They sold the rights to Viaplay because it's how they get the necessary funding.

Instead, the blame lies with UK broadcasters like the BBC and ITV. They seem happy to pay tons for England games but aren’t willing to pay even a fraction for Scottish games, despite their obligation to Scottish viewers. Simon Pitts from STV told us it's because they don't see a big UK-wide commercial return—what a cop-out, right?

This Bill is all about making it mandatory for Scottish matches to be broadcast free on TV, ensuring broadcasters stick to their duties. It's time Scots fans get what they deserve: access to watch and support their team on the big screen. 📺👏

Thanks to my fellow MPs who are backing this Bill. Let's make it happen!"
        }
    ]
}

