            "rewritten_speech": "Hey, could you tell us why the Inter Faith Network (IFN) is being shut down?"
        },
        {
            "speakername": "Felicity Buchan",
            "rewritten_speech": "Thanks for bringing this up, Stephen. We value the Inter Faith Network's work a lot. But here's the thing: recently, they added someone from the Muslim Council of Britain (MCB) to their board, and the UK Government has had a long-standing policy of not working with the MCB. So, we felt it best to pull back funds for now. The IFN needs to find other ways to fund itself because we can’t keep using taxpayer money this way. We love inter-faith work, but IFN needs to be supported by more than just us."
