{
    "speeches": [
        {
            "speakername": "Kevin Hollinrake",
            "rewritten_speech": "Hey everyone, thanks for giving me the floor. So, we've been working non-stop to sort out this mess with the Horizon scandal, trying to make things right for those postmasters who were wronged. We've got an independent inquiry up and running, and have kicked off some redress schemes to speed up compensation. You've probably seen 'Mr Bates vs The Post Office' on TV, but our work on this started way before that aired. \nLast autumn, we announced an optional £600,000 payout for those wrongfully convicted. Just last week, we made it clearer how we're going to overturn those Horizon convictions with new legislation. When this goes into effect, convictions will be cancelled without anyone needing to apply. \nThis is some pretty heavy stuff, and nothing like this has ever been done before. But this scandal is just as unique, so we're going big on the solution. We've got great support from the Horizon compensation advisory board too, and are making sure that compensation gets out fast. We're working with tons of folks who were affected to make sure they get the cash they deserve quickly. For those with full assessment routes, it might take longer, but we're topping up interim payments, like bumping it to £450,000 from £163,000, to help keep things moving.\nWe're doing our best to make first offers of compensation both full and fair. So far, 70% of offers in the GLO scheme were accepted straight off, which makes me think we're on track. There's more detail in our report, which we're dropping today, and I'll keep everyone updated as we keep pushing for justice in this scandal."
