{
    "speeches": [
        {
            "speakername": "Paul Howell",
            "rewritten_speech": "So, why am I up here talking about social media in prisons? It's kind of like being an MP: you've got to juggle between your own experiences and what your community is facing. Today, I’m diving into young people's issues—like knife crime and social media danger. My constituent, Zoey McGill, had her son Jack tragically stabbed to death in 2021. He got a TikTok vid made by one of his murderers, showing off in jail... can you believe it? That’s why I’m involved with The Northern Echo's North East Knife Crime Taskforce. We’ve got parents like Zoey and Theresa Cave, whose son Chris was killed, all pushing for change. They're doing incredible work trying to fix the culture around knives among young folks. But look, allowing inmates to have unchecked social media access is just plain dangerous. It fuels the spread of fake news and radical ideas, so we need to slam the brakes on this. As per gov.uk rules, prisoners shouldn’t have mobile phones or access to social media. Yet, the reality is far from it. It’s no surprise these rules get ignored. That needs to change!"
        },
        {
            "speakername": "Jim Shannon",
            "rewritten_speech": "Great stuff bringing up this issue! I’ve dug into it a bit myself. Isn’t it wild that there’s no actual human right for inmates to be scrolling Insta or Facebook? Rehab is cool and all, but social media access shouldn’t be part of prison life. Let's focus instead on stuff like internet skills that help when they get out."
        },
        {
            "speakername": "Paul Howell",
            "rewritten_speech": "I totally agree, Jim! Prisons let people send emails but only through a service where the message is printed out. And prisons with landlines in cells are doing okay 'cause people don't have to queue for a phone call. Still, allowing mobiles ain't necessary. It only lets them push criminal activities or harass victims. My mate Katherine Fletcher is tackling this with her Prison Media Bill to stop any recordings in prison—dropping a big penalty on folks uploading these too. We need to block prison access to mobile phones altogether."
        },
        {
            "speakername": "Richard Foord",
