        },
        {
            "speakername": "Marion Fellows",
            "rewritten_speech": "I'm pretty miffed that the Secretary of State isn't here. Big thanks to Kevin Hollinrake, though, for working hard on this. But let's be real, Horizon victims aren't getting paid fast enough—they keep saying so. A lot of law talk is making things complicated. Some claims might have been settled for less than they should be. Neil Hudgell thinks this whole compensation thing could drag on for another year or two. Meanwhile, Staunton keeps ranting. Apparently no one's comfortable backing the Secretary up on calling him out. This is our third time asking about his departure and trust is shaky. Sub-postmasters have no faith. We need to fix this and fast, especially as taxpayers' money is at play. 💸"
